---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy — Diamond Web Dev"
  description="Privacy policy for Diamond Web Dev explaining what personal data is collected and how it is used."
  stickyNav={false}
>
  <main class="max-w-screen-md mx-auto px-5 md:px-8 py-16 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-white leading-[1.2] tracking-tight mb-4">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-white/45 text-sm">Last updated: July 2026</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-lg text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
        This policy explains what personal information Diamond Web Dev collects when you use this
        website and contact form, why it is collected, and what happens to it. It is written to
        comply with the UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act
        2018.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          1. Who we are
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          Diamond Web Dev is a sole-trader web development business based in Newcastle, UK. For the
          purposes of UK GDPR, we are the data controller for any personal information collected
          through this website.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mt-3">
          You can contact us at:
          <a
            href="mailto:mikeydiamond@hotmail.co.uk"
            class="text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors"
            >mikeydiamond@hotmail.co.uk</a
          >
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          2. What data we collect and why
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The only personal data we collect is what you voluntarily submit through the contact form:
        </p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Your name</strong> — so we know who we are
              speaking with
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Your email address</strong> — so we can reply
              to your enquiry
            </span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
              <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Your message</strong> — the details of your
              project or question
            </span>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          The legal basis for processing this data is
          <strong class="text-white font-semibold">legitimate interests</strong> (UK GDPR Article
          6(1)(f)) — specifically, to respond to your enquiry and potentially enter into a contract
          with you.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          3. How your data is stored
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          This website is hosted on
          <strong class="text-white font-semibold">GitHub Pages</strong>. The public site files do
          not store your form data. Contact form submissions are sent through
          <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Formspree</strong>, which acts as a data
          processor on our behalf. You can read Formspree's privacy policy at
          <a
            href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors"
            >formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy</a
          >.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mt-3">
          We use <strong class="text-white font-semibold">Google Analytics</strong> to understand
          how visitors use this website (for example, pages viewed and approximate location). Google
          may set cookies or similar technologies as part of this service. You can read Google's
          privacy policy at
          <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors"
            >policies.google.com/privacy</a
          >. The legal basis for this processing is
          <strong class="text-white font-semibold">legitimate interests</strong> (UK GDPR Article
          6(1)(f)) — to improve the website. No data is sold or shared with third parties for
          marketing purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          4. How long we keep your data
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          Form submissions may be retained by Formspree for a period described in their policies
          (see the link above). We process enquiries promptly and do not use your data for
          marketing. If you become a client, your contact details may be retained for the duration
          of the working relationship and up to 6 years afterwards for legal and tax record-keeping
          purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          5. Your rights
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Under UK GDPR you have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed"
              ><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Access</strong> the personal data we hold
              about you</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed"
              ><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Rectify</strong> any inaccurate data</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed"
              ><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Erasure</strong> — request your data be
              deleted</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed"
              ><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Object</strong> to processing of your data</span
            >
          </li>
          <li class="flex gap-3 items-start">
            <span class="mt-[6px] shrink-0 w-[6px] h-[6px] rounded-full bg-accent"></span>
            <span class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed"
              ><strong class="text-white font-semibold">Complain</strong> to the ICO (the UK's data
              protection regulator) at
              <a
                href="https://ico.org.uk"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors">ico.org.uk</a
              ></span
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed mt-4">
          To exercise any of these rights, email us at
          <a
            href="mailto:mikeydiamond@hotmail.co.uk"
            class="text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors"
            >mikeydiamond@hotmail.co.uk</a
          > and we will respond within 30 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">
          6. Changes to this policy
        </h2>
        <p class="text-base text-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          If we make any significant changes to this policy we will update the date at the top of
          this page. We recommend checking back periodically.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-white/10">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-accent hover:text-[#64eca0] transition-colors text-sm font-medium"
      >
        <svg
          width="16"
          height="16"
          viewBox="0 0 16 16"
          fill="none"
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          aria-hidden="true"
        >
          <path
            d="M13 8H3M3 8L7 4M3 8L7 12"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="1.75"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"></path>
        </svg>
        Back to home
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
